      "content": "For those high-stakes meetings, a sharp, conservative look is key to projecting authority. Stick to classic, tailored silhouettes in neutral colors like navy, charcoal, or black; anything too flashy or trendy can undermine your message. Grooming should be immaculate—think neat hair, subtle makeup if you wear it, and polished shoes—to signal attention to detail and seriousness. Remember, in these environments, looking like you belong is almost as important as what you say.",
